t published edition was issued posthumously in 1864, and ultimately seven editions were printed, in varying degrees of quality.\n\nValue characteristics for Goya prints from this series include edition, condition, quality of impression, and plate or subject. At auction the value range is dramatic, with a rare proof of \"Bien te esta\" reaching more than $140,000 to later edition lesser quality impressions selling for less than $500. The subject property, an impression of plate 45 titled \8220Tambien estos\8221, is from the first edition. It  is a good quality impression in very good condition. A national survey of galeries did not locate any prints of this plate, but did locate several first edition prints of other plates in the series. These range from ? to ?. The subject property, is a very good impression in generally good condition.\n"),(ItemDescription,"The composition depicts a room full of wounded soldiers, some lying on the floor and on beds, others seated and standing. Three figures form a triangle in the composition: the seated figure on a bed in the foreground, the standing figure looking over his shoulder in the center and the figure lying on the right in the middle."),(ItemCost,""),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,""),(ItemCondition,"Very good impression in good condition. Upper and lower margins have been trimmed. Mat burn but no foxing and UV light exposure. Remnants of tape residue on reverse of the sheet. Inscribed along bottom margin. \"1-13-37\". Inscription on reverse of sheet L/R corner: ``Disasters of war, 1st edition''. "),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"Etching on wove paper with no watermark."),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,"Series: Los Desastres de la Guerra, first edition"),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,"Unsigned, Composition L/L; no. 25 in U/R margin"),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"Image size: 4 1/2'' x 7 1/2'' (11 1/2 cm. x 19.2 cm); \nPlate impression: 6 1/8'' x 9 1/2'' (15 1/2 cm x 23 1/2 cm)\nSheet size: ???"),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,"19\" x 20 3/4''"),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,"Glaze gilt wood frame"),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,"\"Tambien Estos\" (Also these) from the \"Los desastres de la guerra\" (Disasters of War) series"),(ItemCountryOrNationality,"Spanish"),(ItemArtistDate,"1746-1828"),(ItemArtistOrMaker,"Francisco de Goya "),(ItemItemDate,""),(ItemDateOrPeriod,"1898"),(ItemTypeOfObject,"Print"),(ItemLocation,"Living room"),(ItemInspectionDate,"5/28/09"),(ItemProjectNumber,""),(ItemClient,"Hanson"),(ItemInspector,""),(ItemDataSheetNumber,"5 Hanson #32")], images = [Pic {picSize = ImageSize {dim = TheHeight, size = 3.0, units = Inches}, picCrop = ImageCrop {topCrop = 0, bottomCrop = 0, leftCrop = 0, rightCrop = 0, rotation = 0}, picCaption = "", picImage = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh4.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/SmThoXPWNmI/AAAAAAAAC-I/4U5lZrDuWkA/s640/Goya1.jpg", fileChksum = "10c5286b55fa1707077e866f3c8bbad5", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 640, imageFileHeight = 479, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picEdited = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh4.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/SmThoXPWNmI/AAAAAAAAC-I/4U5lZrDuWkA/s640/Goya1.jpg", fileChksum = "10c5286b55fa1707077e866f3c8bbad5", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 640, imageFileHeight = 479, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picThumb = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheBytes, fileChksum = "9ad9cea61d166acdf7a95b491f2faa36", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 183, imageFileHeight = 137, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picPrinter = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheBytes, fileChksum = "f3b70a8be1092118de3857829f4f6465", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 2405, imageFileHeight = 1800, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picMessages = "<br>\nupdateOriginal http://lh4.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/SmThoXPWNmI/AAAAAAAAC-I/4U5lZrDuWkA/s640/Goya1.jpg"}]}},ReportItem {elemItem = Item {itemName = "", fields = [(ItemAdditionalNotes,"Gallery label on back\n\nJayne Haslem Gallery, The Zither, 9 7/8'' x 10 3/4\" Aquatint and etching, $1500\n\nThe Annex Gallery, The Zither, 24/60 published 1982. $750.\n\nKiechel Fine Art, August, 1940 etching 9 3/4\" x 8\" $1200\n\nEtchings and acquatints of the same era have sold at auction for between $418 and $3200 with the majority in the $1100- $2400 range."),(ItemCashValue,"$1500"),(ItemMarketAnalysis,"Born in Beverly, Massachusettes in 1911 American contemporary artist, Will Barnet is an acclaimed painter and printmaker, who has also taught art at the leading art schools in the U.S.\n\nTrained at the Boston Museum of Fine Arts School and the Art Students League New York, he later taught art at such leading American schools as Yale University, Cornell University, and the Art Students League.\n\nA prolific graphic artist, Barnet changed his style significantly at different points in his career. His earliest works were influenced by expressionism; they were followed by abstract works in the 1950s and 1960s, and finally evolved into more figurative works of silhouetted forms set against geometrically designed backgrounds.\n\nHis work has been exhibited in prominent museums and galleries in the United States and Canada and is included in many prestigious collections, including the Metropolitan Museum of Art and the Guggenheim Museum in New York and the Boston Museum of Fine Arts. The subject property is an example of Barnet's expressionistic early work. A search of auctions and galleries did not turn up any available examples of ``The Bath''. Other aquatints and etchings of this period have sold at auction for between $418 - $3200. At retail, prints of this era have sold for between $750 and $1500 depending on edition. Because ``The Bath'' is currently scarce, the subject property is valued at the high end of this range."),(ItemDescription,""),(ItemCost,"$107"),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,"Davidson Galleries. Mercer Island, WA"),(ItemCondition,"Very good"),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"Acquatint etching"),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,"Edition of 12"),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,"L/R signature, title II ``The Bath''; Edition 12"),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"Sheet: 9 3/4\" x   12\"; Impression: 6 1/2\" x 8 3/4\""),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,""),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,""),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,"The Bath"),(ItemCountryOrNationality,"American"),(ItemArtistDate,"b. 1911"),(ItemArtistOrMaker,"Will Barnet"),(ItemItemDate,""),(ItemDateOrPeriod,"1937, Cole 46"),(ItemTypeOfObject,"Print, Davidson"),(ItemLocation,""),(ItemInspectionDate,""),(ItemProjectNumber,""),(ItemClient,""),(ItemInspector,""),(ItemDataSheetNumber,"6")], images = [Pic {picSize = ImageSize {dim = TheHeight, size = 3.0, units = Inches}, picCrop = ImageCrop {topCrop = 0, bottomCrop = 0, leftCrop = 0, rightCrop = 0, rotation = 0}, picCaption = "", picImage = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh6.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShlbvJW0ffI/AAAAAAAABqc/kv21ucxKpug/s800/DSC_0343.JPG", fileChksum = "2741073cabe851ab5f85e641b3127b12", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 800, imageFileHeight = 632, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picEdited = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh6.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShlbvJW0ffI/AAAAAAAABqc/kv21ucxKpug/s800/DSC_0343.JPG", fileChksum = "2741073cabe851ab5f85e641b3127b12", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, i