le at Kamp Galleries in Winnetka, IL. \nDear Lydia,\nThanks for your inquiry about our Van d. Berg Still Life.  This is the only painting we have by the artist\nand we believe it to be an early example, between the wars, ca 1925.  The dealer price is $2,900.00\n(Retail $5,900.00).  It's a beautiful example of his work, and a good representation of art from that era.\nYou should buy it.\nRegards,\nNick Vahlkamp, mgr.\n- Show quoted text -\n-- \nKamp Gallery\nDrake Hotel Arcade\n140 East Walton Street\nChicago, IL 60611\n312-664-0090\nfax 312-664-0014\n\n\nHis name is also listed on Covington Fine Arts Gallery in Tuscon, AZ.\n6530 E Tanque Verde Rd Suite 140\nTucson Arizona, 85715 USA\nTel: \t(520) 298-7878\nAlso see M. Klein Auctions in Chicago. \n400 W. Hubbard \nChicago Illinois, 60622 USA\nTel: \t312-948-0080\nFax: \t312-948-0090\nListed on Artnet\n"),(ItemCashValue,"$2,900"),(ItemMarketAnalysis,"Willem van den Berg studied art at the Academie voor Beeldende Kunst in The Hague and traveled extensively to Belgium, France, Italy, Austria and England. \nKnown as  a draughtsman, painter and graphic artist, Van Den Berg's style is characterized by a preference for strong closed contours which reflects his interest in Japanese wood block prints. He was director of the Rijksacademie in Amsterdam from 1938 to 1953. He died in Amsterdam in 1970. His paintings are in the collections of museums in Holland, Europe and the United States. The majority of Van Den Berg's works are available through auctions in Amsterdam and Germany. They have sold for between $732 (7.5\" x 5.25\"), Portrait on panel and $6000. Van Den Berg is particularly known for his oil on panel portraits of fishermen and farmers, and these images have brought the highest prices with majority n the $1000-$2500 range. Paintings by the artist comparable to the subject property's pastoral subject that have come up at auction in recent years have all failed to sell indicating a weak market for this subject. A search for Van Den Berg's works for sale in galleries the United States and Europe turned up a single example - an oil on canvas painting still life of garden flowers which is available for $2900 and is the basis for the value conclusion for the subject property."),(ItemDescription,""),(ItemCost,""),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,""),(ItemCondition,"Very good: surface crackelure"),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"oil on panel"),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,""),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,"W. V. D. Berg"),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"11 1/4\" x 15 1/4\" "),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,"16 3/4\" x 20 3/4\""),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,""),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,""),(ItemCountryOrNationality,"Holland/Netherlands"),(ItemArtistDate,"1886-1970"),(ItemArtistOrMaker,"Willem van den Berg"),(ItemItemDate,""),(ItemDateOrPeriod,"early 20th century"),(ItemTypeOfObject,"Painting"),(ItemLocation,""),(ItemInspectionDate,""),(ItemProjectNumber,""),(ItemClient,""),(ItemInspector,""),(ItemDataSheetNumber,"15")], images = [Pic {picSize = ImageSize {dim = TheHeight, size = 3.0, units = Inches}, picCrop = ImageCrop {topCrop = 0, bottomCrop = 0, leftCrop = 0, rightCrop = 0, rotation = 0}, picCaption = "", picImage = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh6.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShwmvncL_sI/AAAAAAAABww/33e5fwELMLY/s720/DSC03318.JPG", fileChksum = "49dd80467b4515462303f794b29ffe58", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 720, imageFileHeight = 504, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picEdited = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh6.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShwmvncL_sI/AAAAAAAABww/33e5fwELMLY/s720/DSC03318.JPG", fileChksum = "49dd80467b4515462303f794b29ffe58", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileT