 print making. Known primarily as an abstract impressionist, Burkhardt also worked in a figurative style. Born in Switzerland, Burkhardt came to the United States in ??. He moved to Los Angeles in 1937 and was a well known and well regarded figure in the West Coast art scene. Burkhardt\8217s work has received recent attention due to two major projects, a retrospective of his work mounted at the University Gallery at California State University Northridge, and a comprehensive exhibition of his 1960s paintings presented at the Jack Rutberg Gallery in Los Angeles in 2008-2009. These projects have brought renewed public attention to the artists\8217s work reflected in a greater wolume of sales at auction.\n\nValue characteristics for Burhardt prints include date, size, condition and quality. In the case of his works on paper, a review of auction results in the past five years indicates that earlier works from the 1930s and 1940s appear to be more desirable, reaching higher prices than later drawings from the 1970s and 1980s. The subject property is an earlier work in the abstract style in very good condition. A survey of retail offerings located two pastel works on paper, one offered for $7,125 and the second for $14,000\n"),(ItemDescription,"Abstract composition of three figures rendered in colors on ivory paper"),(ItemCost,""),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,""),(ItemCondition,"Very Good"),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"graphite and pastel on paper"),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,""),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,"Signed, dated lower center quadrant"),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"26\" x 19 1/2\""),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,"27\" x 20 3/4\""),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,"Red painted and gilt wood frame"),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,""),(ItemCountryOrNationality,""),(ItemAr