950 at Davidsons.\nDeux Nus recently sold at Davidson's for $950\nDeux Nus offered for sale at Figaro Gallery for $1800.\nDavidson's recently sold a print for $950"),(ItemCashValue,"$1,800"),(ItemMarketAnalysis,"A French painter, illustrator and printmaker, member of the group of artists called the Nabis and afterward a leader of the Intimists; he is generally regarded as one of the greatest colourists of modern art. He also produced lithographs and dry-point. In the 1920s he undertook a series of paintings on one of his most famous themes\8212a nude in a bath, the subject of this lithograph. Les Baigneuses  was probably engraved for Ambrose Vollard who was planing an Album de Nus with various artists. Value characteristics for Bonnard prints include quality of impression, state and condition. A search of auction prices indicate that lithographs of nudes by Bonnard have sold for between $1200 and $2880. At the retail level lithographs of nudes, including 2 examples of Les Baigneuses, have sold and are available at the retail level for between $950 and $1800. Les Baigneuses is currently available the The Figaro Gallery and is the basis for estimating the subject property's Replacement Value. \n\n"),(ItemDescription,"Impressionistic rendering of two nude women situated in a landscape. One lies on the grass while the other stands in profile next to a small tree or bush. Rendered in a loose, impressionistic line. "),(ItemCost,"$232"),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,"Davidson Galleries, Mercer Island, WA"),(ItemCondition,"Very Good. Nothing to note."),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"Drypoint and roulette. Handmade wove paper (Japanese paper)"),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,"Edition of 50"),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,""),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"Sheet: 26 cm x 31 cm 10\" x 12\"; Impression:  16 cm x 23.2 cm  6 1/2\" x 23.2 cm. 9 1/4\" \t\t\t\n"),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,""),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,""),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,"Deux Nus (Les Baigneuses)"),(ItemCountryOrNationality,"French"),(ItemArtistDate,"1867-1947"),(ItemArtistOrMaker,"Pierre Bonnard"),(ItemItemDate,""),(ItemDateOrPeriod,"c. 1927-29"),(ItemTypeOfObject,"Print (Davidson)"),(ItemLocation,""),(ItemInspectionDate,""),(ItemProjectNumber,""),(ItemClient,""),(ItemInspector,""),(ItemDataSheetNumber,"6, Hanson #18")], images = [Pic {picSize = ImageSize {dim = TheHeight, size = 3.0, units = Inches}, picCrop = ImageCrop {topCrop = 0, bottomCrop = 0, leftCrop = 0, rightCrop = 0, rotation = 0}, picCaption = "", picImage = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh3.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShlbvtyXvFI/AAAAAAAABqk/cUWgS7DuEH8/s800/DSC_0345.JPG", fileChksum = "86cc8540086f6ff5101b3f370297ae92", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 800, imageFileHeight = 624, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picEdited = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh3.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShlbvtyXvFI/AAAAAAAABqk/cUWgS7DuEH8/s800/DSC_0345.JPG", fileChksum = "86cc8540086f6ff5101b3f370297ae92", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 800, imageFileHeight = 624, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picThumb = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheBytes, fileChksum = "33c6d8738ebaf0cf5ede0f8b1903896d", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 179, imageFileHeight = 140, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picPrinter = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheBytes, fileChksum = "66cd9fdb2fc7a56c64c2fc4f760b85e3", fileBytes = Nothing, fileMessages = []}, imageFileType = JPEG, imageFileWidth = 2308, imageFileHeight = 1800, imageFileMaxVal = 255}), picMessages = "<br>\nupdateOriginal http://lh3.ggpht.com/_s-XE562xJtM/ShlbvtyXvFI/AAAAAAAABqk/cUWgS7DuEH8/s800/DSC_0345.JPG"}]}},ReportItem {elemItem = Item {itemName = "", fields = [(ItemAdditionalNotes,"Jean-Luc Baroni, Ltd.of London has a drawing for sale. As yet I have not located galleries that sell his prints..\n\nMost recent sale of print, Elefanten, ein Lowe unde ein Eber, 33.2 x 47.7 cm. Bassenge, 04/06/09 $1050\n\nEtchings by are available at Spaightwood Galleries for between $1750- $4500. Most are much smaller than the subject property. "),(ItemCashValue,"$4,500"),(ItemMarketAnalysis,"Known as a Mannerist painter, draughtsman and printmaker, Battista Franco spent the first years of his independent career in Rome, but by 1536 had settled in Florence. Franco is better known, and has usually been more highly regarded, as a draughtsman rather than as a painter. He is also well known for his etching having produced over 100 during his life-time. An assiduous copyist, among his drawings and etchings are numerous studies of antique subjects, usually taken from reliefs on Roman sarcophagi. According to the Illustrated Bartsch, The Deluge was likely after a work designed by Polidoro da Caravaggio.\n\nValue characteristics of prints include state, quality of impression, edition size, subject matter and condition. The subject property is in good condition and is a fine impression. A search for etchings by this artist indicate that the primary  market for this artist is in Europe with most sales taking place at Galerie Bassenge Kunst Und Buchauktionene and Reiss & Sohn in Berlin.  Prints of similar biblical subjects, size, quality of impression, condition and subject matter range from $1401-$2424. The subject property is most comparable in quality of impression to prints at the high end of this range. A search of etchings by the artist in galleries in the United States only turned up a single venue, Spaightwood Galleries in Upton, Massachusetts where a number etchings are available for between $1750-$4500. Most of the etchings available for sale are considerably smaller than the subject property. The etching most closely approximating the subject property in size and quality of impression is available for $4,500 and is the basis for estimating the subject property's replacement value\n"),(ItemDescription,"A biblical scene of the flood said to be taken from a work by Polidoro da Caravaggio depicting people fleeing to higher ground to escape the rising waters. Figures are seen pulling themselves from the water and helping women and children to higher ground. The sky is heavy with clouds with heavy vertical lines depicting torrents of rain. The arc is shown in the middle-ground of the composition. "),(ItemCost,""),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,""),(ItemCondition,"Good: Some stains and creases. Good impression."),(ItemMediumMaterialsTechniques,"Etching"),(ItemVerso,""),(ItemRecto,""),(ItemPhotographNumbers,""),(ItemSignatureInscriptionsMarkings,"Signed in the plate lower left, Battista Franco Inu"),(ItemItemDepth,""),(ItemItemWidth,""),(ItemItemHeight,""),(ItemItemMeasurement,"Sheet: 10 1/2\" x 17\" (27 cm x 43 cm)"),(ItemFrameDepth,""),(ItemFrameWidth,""),(ItemFrameHeight,""),(ItemFrameMeasurement,"25 1/4\" x 30 1/4\""),(ItemSupportBaseFrame,"Glazed silver gilt wood frame"),(ItemSubjectOrTitle,"The Deluge, Le deluge universel, 3, Bartsch"),(ItemCountryOrNationality,"Italy"),(ItemArtistDate,"1498-1561"),(ItemArtistOrMaker,"Giovanni Battista Franco Inu"),(ItemItemDate,""),(ItemDateOrPeriod,"16th century"),(ItemTypeOfObject,"Print"),(ItemLocation,""),(ItemInspectionDate,""),(ItemProjectNumber,""),(ItemClient,""),(ItemInspector,""),(ItemDataSheetNumber,"7, Hanson #66")], images = [Pic {picSize = ImageSize {dim = TheHeight, size = 3.0, units = Inches}, picCrop = ImageCrop {topCrop = 0, bottomCrop = 0, leftCrop = 0, rightCrop = 0, rotation = 0}, picCaption = "", picImage = Just (ImageFile {imageFile = File {fileSource = TheURI "http://lh5.ggpht.com/_s-