 {elemItem = Item {itemName = "", fields = [(ItemAdditionalNotes,"Painted screens available at Ark Antiques are and Edo period, 6 panel screen, 4'6\" high in very good condition and very good quality offered for $2600.\nA small screen, approx. 3'5\" high, 6 panels,  Japanese, 19th century of birds, duck, chickens and foliage available for $1800.\n\n8 panel painted Chinese screen sold at Millea Brothers for $2000 + BP 10/29/06\n\n"),(ItemCashValue,"$2,000"),(ItemMarketAnalysis,"This screen was produced for export to the Western markets.  Vintage screens from China are available from importers and at estate sales and regional auction houses. Value characteristics include age, quality of painting, size and condition. The subject property was purchased at an art sale at California State University at Northridge. Therefore the appropriate market level for this piece are works found at high-end consignment stores and regional auction houses. Vintage screens similar to the subject property in size, age and quality are available for between $575 and $3,500. The subject property's relatively large-size and good quality make it most comparable to examples in the middle of this value range. A pair of four-panel painted Chinese screens depicting boaters on river amid mountains sold at an Millea Brothers auction house in New Jersey for $2,000 is the basis for the subject property's replacement value.\n "),(ItemDescription,"A six-panel painted screen of ink and colors on paper depicting a landscape of misty mountains, tiny villages and boaters along a river. It is mounted on a lacquer frame. "),(ItemCost,""),(ItemFax,""),(ItemTel,""),(ItemCity,""),(ItemAddress,""),(ItemExhibitionsAndPublications,""),(ItemProvenance,"California State University at Northridge"),(ItemCondition,"Good: First panel: buckling, a hole in upper quarter; second panel, some slight buckling; third panel: one small buckle in center; fourth panel: horizontal buckling with creases and some loss of pigment; fift